    {
      "_id": "4Mz2MfAj0qrjSWX0",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Spirit Anchors",
      "sort": 0,
      "type": "action",
      "system": {
        "actionType": {
          "value": "passive"
        },
        "actions": {
          "value": null
        },
        "category": "defensive",
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>While any of his four anchors exists</strong> (Belshallam B23, Castothrane D1, Nihil D14, Zev Ravenka F11), Mithrodar re-forms 1d4 days after 'destruction' — he <strong>cannot be permanently defeated</strong>. He can chain a new non-mindless evil creature as a replacement anchor (constructs never; Ildervok never — Zon-Kuthon's writ outranks his; <em>Sial or Laori would serve nicely</em>). Per anchor destroyed, the curse sheds a layer: 1 — safe sleep (and the castle screams: all Scarwall undead +4 vs. vitality); 2 — the Aura of Menace ends; 3 — wall-spirits stop roaming; 4 — the <em>unhallow</em> and dimensional lock fall, and he can finally die.</p>"
        },
        "publication": {
          "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
          "authors": "",
          "license": "OGL",
          "remaster": true
        },
        "rules": [],
        "slug": null,
        "traits": {
          "rarity": "common",
          "value": []
        }
      },
      "_key": "!actors.items!mithrodarChain01.4Mz2MfAj0qrjSWX0"
    },
    {
      "_id": "cE0IGqBWbKWxK8LG",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Chained Spirit",
      "sort": 0,
      "type": "action",
      "system": {
        "actionType": {
          "value": "passive"
        },
        "actions": {
          "value": null
        },
        "category": "defensive",
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Incorporeal; resistance all 15 (except force/ghost touch/vitality); the curse's soultrap (see the Curse page) is <em>his</em> reach — he assaults any spirit entering the castle, Zellara above all.</p>"
        },
        "publication": {
