      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Scarwall's castellan, hanged in his own chains when Kazavon fell — now the <strong>chained spirit</strong> at the heart of the curse, enthroned in the Great Hall (C14). Every bound soul in the walls is his to spend. <strong>Destroying him (after the four anchors) frees every trapped soul, lifts the curse — and wakes <em>Serithtial</em>.</strong></p>",
